definition.value: A one-carbon compound in which the carbon is joined only to a single oxygen. It is a colourless, odourless, tasteless, toxic gas.
A homopolymer macromolecule obtained by polymerisation of vinyl alcohol.
A member of the class of  dihydrofurans that is disulfane in which both hydrogen's are substituted by 2-methyl-4,5-dihydrofuran-3-yl groups. It is a flavouring agent found in meat.
A dihydroxy-1,3,5-triazine consisting of ammelide bearing an N-isopropyl substituent.
An amino acid opine resulting from the formal reductive condensation of the amino group of L-arginine with the keto group of 2-oxopentanedioic acid.
